    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-15T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="997"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d997">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102F/8: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-16T11:00:00+09:00"
                            >August 16, 1940—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 17—5:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>702. Reference Peiping’s despatch No. 2460, January 17, 1940.<note n="11"
                        xml:id="d997fn11">Not printed.</note> The British Embassy is now authorized
                    to propose to the Japanese Government that a regular steamship service to Sharp
                    Peak [Fukien], be allowed to pass the Japanese blockade.</p>
                <p>Please instruct as to whether the Department desires me to make informal
                    representations to the Foreign Office on humanitarian grounds and because of the
                    need of Americans at Foochow for such service.<note n="12" xml:id="d997fn12">The
                        Department so instructed in its telegram No. 315, August 19, 6 p.m.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Sent to the Department via Peiping.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department, repeated to Chungking, Foochow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
